  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the robata grill to 400 degrees Fahrenheit",
    "Season the duck legs with salt, black pepper, and minced garlic",
    "In a large bowl, combine the duck legs, thyme, rosemary, and bay leaves",
    "Drizzle the olive oil over the duck legs and mix well",
    "Place the duck legs on the robata grill and cook for 30 minutes per side",
    "After cooking, let the duck legs rest for 10 minutes before serving",
    "Serve the duck confit with robata grill sauce spooned over the top",
    "Ensure poultry is cooked to an internal temperature of 74°C / 165°F (juices run clear, no pink remaining) before serving."
  ],
